OL,4,CTwo-year degrees to lower tuition fees
OL,5, Students in England are going to be
OL,6, offered degrees in two years with a
OL,7, B#5,500 saving in tuition fees, says
OL,8, the universities minister Jo Johnson.
OL,10,FUndergraduate courses will be condensed
OL,11,Finto "accelerated" degrees, with fees
OL,12,F20% less than a three-year course.
OL,14,FMr Johnson said he wants to "break the
OL,15,Fmould" of a system in which three-year
OL,16,Fdegrees have "crowded out" any more
OL,17,Fflexible ways of studying.
OL,19,FThe Office for Fair Access says the
OL,20,Fplan could help to widen opportunities.
